author: @sudeetiambale548
text: This might be an unpopular opinion, but I think Seungmin stood out a lot in this video {to me}. He shone so much, especially in the part after the first chorus, where they were rapping, the "BLAH BLAH" part, and when Changbin was rapping, the way Seungmin lip-synced the rap got me. And his vocals are simply so melodious, it looks like he is not even trying but he sounds so good. I am a singer myself and have been studying music for the past 10 years, and I swear, his vocal parts are NOT easy. The way he sings it easily shows his professionalism as a singer. And, his dancing has come a long way. Especially now, in the LALALALALA era, the black outfit stage was owned by him. You can see the improvement here only. His visuals are so good, and his facial features are so pleasing. And due to his height, his and Hyunjin's proportions are the best in SKZ according to me {no hate for any other members}. He is a lowkey all-rounder: he raps, sings, dances, and has stage presence too. This is absolutely out of topic, but he is pretty intelligent too. I admire him for his awe-inspiring journey and love him for what he is. Again, I am just voicing my opinion and I love all the members. LOVE STRAYKIDS

author: @kittyc997
text:
Love Stray Kids! Love Dance Practice videos! And this is my ALL TIME FAVE choreography! There are tons of greats (Easy, I am You, I could go on all day), but this one just has EVERYTHING. 
Precision, variety, and every member doing what they do best. Hyunjin being smooth, Channie being so happy, Han and his swag, etc. 
The domino line and 3 groups doing a similar echo earlier are just so clever and fit the song perfectly. 
And every time Felix comes in "dun dun dun dun, hey" I can't help but grin. This video brightens my day every time. 
❤😁❤😁❤

author: @melodiouslyy
text:
omg this was just SO GOOD. the choreo for this one seems very difficult, but they all made it look so easy! here are some details/easter egg tidbits i caught while watching
0:04 changbin "controlling" felix + hyunjins movements with his hand which looks really cool
0:18 just chan vibing as he waits to come back in LOL
0:19 hyunjin leans back into changbin who hugs him from behind which was so cute <3
0:25 lee know and I.N share a high five 🥺
0:27 binnie puts his hand on hyunjin's shoulder
0:32 chan and seungmin fist bump which i think is quite purposeful since chan kind of "transfers" the vocal lines to seungmin, who sings next
1:03 HYUNJIN SLAPS CHAN'S BUTT BAHAHHAHA
1:21 smol lee know hop 
1:22 not so much an observation but wHY IS HANS "BLAH BLAH" SO ADDICTING BYE
1:24 idk if im the only one who didnt notice this the first watch around but they all hold up an 👌sign w their hands here
1:29 tiny steps 
2:04 ok who gave the choreographer the right to make this part SO INCREDIBLY SATISFYING.
2:15 I.N coming up with a smile hes SO CUTE 
2:16 chan shovelling
2:17 hyunjin slaps chans butt pt 2
2:39 i.n's little :O
2:45 sir i need you to get that tongue back in your mouth before i combust
2:53 hyunjin reaches up to adjust his hat. this isn't really an easter egg, mostly just him absolutely killing in that hat 
2:55 hans tiny shift backwards then a smol spin 
3:13 han almost loses balance AHHAAHA and he's grinning about it it's so cute that he's having the time of his life while dancing
3:19 i think it's hyunjin? who lets out the "aHh" in exhaustion since he's the one pulling off his hat? I'm not sure though
but yes these were all the ones that I noticed while watching! if there are any others do let me know, the amount of detail in this choreo is insane!! 
also omg this was just wayy too good. the choreo for this one seems very difficult, but they all made it look so easy! especially for hyunjin, his movements were so fluid and natural. my baby IN improved in dancing sm too 🥺 and minho got so many lines which i love <3

once a stay, always a stay <3

black trousers, white shirt with red pattern: Hyunjin (Main Dancer, Lead Rapper, Vocalist, Visual)
all in white: Han (Main Rapper, Producer, Lead Vocalist)
white shirt, blonde hair, black beanie: Felix (Main Dancer, Lead Rapper, Vocalist)
white hoodie: Seungmin (Main Vocalist)
black shirt, white trousers: I.N (Vocalist, Maknae)

author: @zzzy98.7
text: I don’t know if anyone said this or maybe i’m wrong but i cathed some parts in the choreo wich i’ve seen in other dance practice videos. If this is true i think that is really cool and it makes it more fun to watch cause you see some moves you’ve already seen. This is really one of the best choreos of Stray Kids in my opinion and from start to end their energy never decrease. I love how each member has a lot of time to shine in the song and in the dance. Personally i think this song and dance has some really strong title track vibe but i think because the dance is so hard and the moves are big it looks like it is harder to sing it live so maybe thats why they didnt choose this as title track but either way both Thunderous and Domino is 1000% fire. Actually the whole album is fire. I’ve been a stay for more than 2 years now and i never came across to a bad Stray Kids song( all thanks to 3racha). It just keeps getting better and better. I feel really proud to see them getting the attention and love they always deserved.  I am so lucky that i found them, they helped me a lot throughout a lot of difficult time in my life. Thanks to them i am now in my dream university cause they thaught me to never give up on my dreams. I hope they know how much they mean to Stays. I am so glad i chose to join this family.

text:
Choreographer: How many formation changes do you want?
Stray Kids: *Yes*

(P.S. I know Lee Know choreographs a lot of their songs, but they have others too) Anyway, I just love this. Whatever studio this is with the red background always creates a great aesthetic for their practice videos. And this choreo is just...oof, entertained by every second, some moves are so dynamic - I love the blocking with each member "falling" on the main "Domino" hook and then the way the subsequent moves progress through the group...like that is not easily done. Wow, and on of the last hooks, they have Chan in the middle since his vocals "stop" the effect...AHH SO SMART! Also, Chan's curling move at 2:15 XD

text:
The choreography is awesome, and what makes it even better is how skz manage to keep stable in singing and rapping. 

Also I have to say that this choreo is so Lee Know style. Not saying that others is bad though, coz honestly they're all so good and so synchronized with such fast paced choreo. But there's something that makes Lee Know dance so satisfying to watch. I love how he put some tiny details which make the dance moves even better. For example 01:17, he is the only one who have that kind of almost falling move, hence it connect with the next move better (I don't really know how to describe it, hopefully it's at least understandable). 01:28, it's a little bit similar to krumping where he's using chest and shoulder instead of only arms.

text:
Alright this is probably on purpose since there are so many parts of it but these dance moves remind me A LOT of the ones from "Easy":
0:23 Jeongins part reminds me of the "Ta ta ta" move 
0:44 "eodil bwado neomo easy" move in the pre chorus
0:50 (might be a stretch) Hyunjins move reminds me of Hans "I don't care" part 
1:00 Felix's "eopgo nolja" part
1:08 "eonjelado nan" move in the chorus
1:37 Chans "look at me now" part
1:40 Minsung doing the same move as in Easy (the beginning)
1:41 I.Ns "yeah!" part

Also moves that remind me of "Thunderous": 
0:41 "sorikkun" part
1:36 Chans "I know we'll burn forever" part
1:48 reminds me of Felix's "kundeuri wasseoyo" part
3:12 reminds me of Felix's "kundeuri wasseoyo" part too

text:
Я поражена сложностью хореографии и такой синхронности. Я никогда не сомневалась в высоком уровне парней в танцах, но это... Это просто безумие. Нереально сложная хоряга исполнена на высшем уровне, как же я горжусь ростом парней. 
Кстати, стэй, голосуйте пожалуйста в приложении Whosfan и на сайте mwave, а также стримьте песни на Спотифае и Эпл Мьюзик. Если кому-то нужна помощь-напишите, я помогу разобраться, это совесем не сложно и быстро, а парням принесёт еще победы. Спасибо стэй, что поддерживаете парней, не забывайте пить водичку и хорошо кушать, хорошего дня~

author: @AhsokaJackson
text:
Eyyy!! Holy cow, this is INTENSE. It’s exhausting just to watch…yet it also gets me pumped, haha. Between the level of energy and the density of the choreography, that must take some real stamina and also focus. I continue to be impressed by these gentlemen. The fact that they’re not just singers who can dance a bit—nah, they really go in on BOTH—and the fact that they ALSO are on the writing and choreographing sections of the process rather than only performing material written or choreographed by others. 

Those are four different fields all on their own (dancing, singing [& rapping, which is really its own skill!], song writing, choreography), not counting the sub-skills needed in each. 

IM-PRES-SIVE!

Now, please excuse me while
I go watch the music video, because this is hella catchy, haha. ^^

author: @sabrinag7908
text:
Parts of this video that I personally think deserve to be appreciated:

0:02 - The very start of this choreo is so smooth and satisfying. I'm obsessed.
0:10 - Changbin's kick
0:11 - 0:14 - Hyunjin's facial expressions
0:12 - 0:16 - Lix's beanie falling over his eyes🥺
0:16 - 0:21 - There is something so satisfying about the way Jeongin dances here. I'm honestly mesmerized.
0:21 - 0:25 - Followed by his facial expressions here. You can really see just how much he's grown and improved.  
0:19 - 0:24 - Jinnie and Binnie🥺🥺
0:17 - 0:26 - Whatever it is that Chan's doing, I busted a lung. I love him
0:53 - 0:54 - The way Hyunjin does this move
0:55 - 0:56 - The way Minho does this move
1:00 - CHANGBIN'S CLAP?? HELLO??
1:01 - The way Chnagbin starts this move and the rest of the members follow? Flawless.
1:03 - 1:04 - Hyunjin spanking Chan
1:04 - 1:10 - Just a moment of appreciation for Seungmin center
1:04 - 1:10 - The way Changbin does this part *WHEW*
1:10 - 1:15 - The energy this man radiates is so attractive. I need a minute.
1:21 - 1:24 - The way Seungmin does this part
1:24 - Look at how smoothly Lix makes his way into the center. 
1:34 - Chan spanking Jeongin
1:36 - Minho's facial expressions
1:36 - 1:42 - Hyunjin. That's the tweet.
1:44 - THIS. PART.
1:45 - 1:47 - Chan and Minho's facial expressions
1:48 - How smoothly Hyunjin moves into his place
1:52 - 1:54 - J-Jeongin?
1:55 - The way Hyunjin does this move
2:05 - THIS ARE WE FUCKING KIDDING??
2:14 - Jisung's facial expressions
2:19 - I saw that tongue, Yang Jeongin
2:31 - 2:39 - Hyunjin. Good lord
2:41 - 2:53 - Name a flaw. I'll wait.
2:46 - Hyunjin and Jeongin.
2:52 - 2:53 - THE STOMPS. THE SYNCRONIZATION. FLAWLESS.
2:53 - 2:58 - Chan, Minho, Hyunjin, Han, and Jeongin's facial expressions
3:01 - 3:03 - The way Hyunjin and Jeongin do this part
3:04 - 3:18 - They all look like they're having so much fun and I'm so in love

With all this being said, please love and support our 8 boys!!

author: @GraeSloane
text:
So this is an absolutely insanely good and difficult choreo! - I should know, I've been watching it on a loop since it was posted lol

Like not only the whole choreo (the formations and images) is crazy but each individual member's choreo is super hard and insanely detailed and precise and they just completely killed it!!! 

Jeongin made incredible progress in dancing since he started working out, so did Seungmin thanks to his diligence with practice. 
The facial expressions, especially Chan, Changbin, Felix and Jeongin are amazing. 
Their energy is through the roof, all of them! 
The song is bangers (but we already knew that) 
They managed to do the domino effect (dance in canon - dance the same moves but one by one at different times) and still be perfectly syncronized for the other parts of the choreo 

And I am just in awe of all there is to unpack in this (Chan mopping the floor and making way for Felix's "DAN DAN DAN DAN"s, Felix's beanie covering his eyes while he just keeps on dancing, Hyunjin making Changbin give him a back hug on the side while they wait their turn with Chan next to them dancing like a worm, the apparent chaos when they're swinging precariously on one foot at the end, even the fact that... this is the last Dance Practice with Hyunjin's long hair T.T _ a perfect video all around) 


Do yourself a favour and watch this a million times with me! 
Why only have 3mn 24sec of pure bliss when you can have more hehe

для бейби-стэй

Бан Чан – чёрные шорты, чёрная футболка и кепка.

Лино – чёрные штаны с тремя полосками, чёрная футболка и чёрная шапка.

Со Чанбин – в чёрных штанах с тремя полосками, в чёрной кофте с длинными рукавами и в чёрной кепке.

Хван Хёнджин – в чёрных штанах с тремя полосками, в белой футболке и в чёрной панамке.

Хан Джисон – единственный во всём белом (кроме кроссовок).

Ли Феликс – в чёрных штанах без полосок, в белой футболке и в шапке celinе.

Ким Сынмин – чёрные штаны, белая кофта с длинными рукавами и серым капюшоном, без головного убора.

Ян Чонин – белые штаны, чёрная шутболка, без головного убора (в чёрной повязке на голову).

author: @pratisthalama4656
text:
Usually in groups, you’d expect one or two members to be not quite at the level as the others, but Stray Kids genuinely astounds me because all of their dancing is at an extremely high standard to the point that it actually takes a close analysis and research to find out who the ‘assigned’ dancers are. And this also applies for their singing and rapping skills as well.  Some seem to be under the impression that good vocals = the ability to reach high notes, and although skz certainly has members able to sing those notes, good vocals is more about showcasing incredibly stable and clear vocals which ALL members of skz do fantastically. I don’t need to touch on the rapping, we’ve all seen every member  at some point prove that they are than capable in spitting out some bars.

Long story short, skz is incredible, this video is just another piece of evidence to support that.

author: @Librarian2406
text:
The choreo is not only pleasing and stunning to look at, but the depictions are spot on, I hv seen this alot in skz choreography that the choreo is "smart" and "creative" and apart from that the intricacies at certain points in the choreo is remarkable, and the contrast between the intricate and loud over the top choreo at other parts, is perfectly balanced! And after all of this, their execution of moves is getting better and better every comeback,  jeongin specifically has TREMENDOUSLY improved his dancing, and I hv always admired his stage precense anyway. Apart  from this I love the fact that the choreos are a good balance of hard and fluid. This gives a lot of variety and fun to the chireo. I also think their controll and energy is very spot on, as in its neither too much nor too less, making it look seemeless, and effortless, along with not looking lousy. This is hard to pull off!
I am happy that with every cb the dance factor gains more and more spotlight!
